North Korea Says They Will “Never” Disarm Unilaterally Without Confidence
North Korea’s foreign minister told the United Nations on Saturday that further sanctions deepened their distrust of the United States and it was not possible for the country to give up its nuclear weapons unilaterally in such circumstances.
Ri Yong Ho told the World Organization’s annual General Assembly that North Korea had taken “significant steps in the past year to show its goodwill,” for example by stopping nuclear weapons and missile tests, dismantling nuclear test facilities, and promising not to spread nuclear weapons and nuclear weapons.
“We don’t see any similar response from the United States,” he said.
